# 🛒 NovaMart — E-Commerce Store | Internship Project Plan

## Store Name

> **NovaMart**

---

## Overview

A fully functional, professionally designed e-commerce web application built for internship **Project 1**.
- **Store** → Customer-facing website (browse, cart, checkout, profile)
- **Admin Panel** → Completely separate application (own login, own routes, isolated from store)

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────────────┐
│   STORE (Customer Frontend) │    │  ADMIN PANEL (Separate App)  │
│   frontend/                 │    │  admin-panel/                │
│   localhost:5500            │    │  localhost:5501 (or /admin)  │
└────────────┬────────────────┘    └────────────┬─────────────────┘
             │ REST API + Socket.IO              │ REST API + Socket.IO
             ▼                                  ▼
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  Express.js Server  (Node.js)                  │
│                  + Socket.IO (Real-time events)                │
│                                                                │
│  /api/auth/*      → Customer auth                              │
│  /api/products/*  → Public product routes                      │
│  /api/cart/*      → Customer cart                              │
│  /api/orders/*    → Customer orders                            │
│  /api/admin/*     → Admin-only routes (separate JWT required)  │
└───────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────┘
                            │ Mongoose ODM
                            ▼
                    ┌───────────────┐
                    │   MongoDB     │
                    │  (local       │
                    │   Compass)    │
                    └───────────────┘
```

- **Frontend**: HTML5 + Vanilla CSS (glassmorphism, dark mode) + Vanilla JS + Socket.IO Client
- **Backend**: Node.js + Express.js (REST API) + Socket.IO (WebSockets)
- **Database**: **MongoDB Local (Compass)** with **Mongoose ODM**
- **Customer Auth**: JWT (`JWT_SECRET`)
- **Admin Auth**: Separate JWT (`ADMIN_JWT_SECRET`) — completely independent

---

